• Apply the understanding of the client's business and industry to identify areas of audit significance, assesses risks and the nature of the errors;
• Identify unusual/unexpected transactions, and explain important matters to staff;
• Supervise, motivate and develop the team of junior audit staff;
• Liaise with FDI clients or participate in Meetings with engagement team and client;
• Proactively assist Manager/ Senior Manager/ Director in searching and advising issues relating to professional and accounting/auditing technical knowledge;
• Manage timelines, resources and quality of audit engagement;
• Be responsible for training, managing and reviewing the works of junior personnel.
2. Non-audit (30%)
Provide all of the following services to our FDI clients as senior staff
• Review of monthly/Quarterly Financial Statements;
• Review of tax returns (e.g., VAT, PIT, CIT, FCT);
• Manage client relationships, identify risk and provide client with advice relating to accounting and taxation matter.

As a member of our legal advisory team, you will be responsible for – inter alia – the following tasks:
• Advising clients on ongoing legal issues of their business at the highest level of quality, commitment and effectiveness
• Drafting and reviewing legal documents (memos, advice, legal opinions and due-diligence reports), contracts and other agreements, licensing application files (e.g., application files, business licenses, etc.);
• Building, maintaining, and leveraging existing relationships, with the law firm’s stakeholders, client portfolio, and local administrative authorities;
• Independently handling client matters (attending meetings and communicating directly with clients, suppliers, and other parties) across multiple areas of business (manufacturing, labour, real estate, technology, R&D, renewable energies, infrastructure, retail/FMCG, etc.);
• Carrying out in-depth legal research and staying abreast of current legal developments, regulations, and laws;
• Contributing to the firms marketing/BD workstreams (e.g., drafting newsletters, legal updates and articles on legal issues; preparing materials for events, etc.);
• Leading and supervising junior team members during the implementation of advisory/project work and training other lawyers in practical and theoretical aspects of transactional and advisory work;
• Working closely together with the firm’s management (under supervision of senior lawyers) for the benefit of the firm’s practice and its clients.

